{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Transparency and member resources · OIATC{% endblock %}
{% block description %}OIATC's transparency program brings documentation discipline to members' right to see how their governments and systems work: responsible disclosure of digital-systems issues, and support for the independent, member-led Transparency Circle.{% endblock %}
{% block og_title %}Transparency and member resources{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}OIATC's transparency program: documentation discipline, responsible disclosure, and support for the independent, member-led Transparency Circle.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-program-member-resources{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}{% include 'partials/funder-styles.html.twig' %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="fund-wrap fund-wrap--narrow">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">OIATC program</p>
  <h1>Transparency and member resources</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">Members have the right to see how their governments and systems work. This program is the documentation discipline OIATC brings to that right: responsible disclosure of digital-systems issues, sourced carefully, and steady support for the independent, member-led transparency work that members now lead on their own.</p>

  <div class="fund-body">
    <p>The work is documentation, not grievance. Responsible disclosure, and the documentation method behind it, are ordinary instruments of accountable government: we assemble the facts carefully, source every one, and present them with the discipline a member or an official can rely on. The member-led records and transparency work itself belongs to the members. OIATC supports it at arm's length and does not run it.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The work, by stage</h2>
    <ul class="fund-links">
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> <a href="/disclosure/sagamok-portal">Responsible disclosure</a> <span>· a member-portal exposure, disclosed responsibly</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>An independent home for the members' transparency work</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p><strong>Independent, member-led transparency.</strong> The treaty-wide and community transparency work that members lead now has its own independent home: the Robinson Huron Treaty Members' Transparency Circle, a member-led group of beneficiaries across the 21 Robinson Huron Treaty First Nations. OIATC supports independent, member-led transparency as a principle. The Circle is independent of OIATC. We neither run it nor govern it, and it is not affiliated with us. We point to its front door so members can find it; the questions and the work are the members' own.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fund-cta">
      <a class="fund-cta__btn" href="https://rhtcircle.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit the Transparency Circle &rarr;</a>
      <span class="fund-cta__addr"><a href="https://rhtcircle.ca/treaty-wide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The treaty-wide ask &rarr;</a></span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The fundable next step</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>Funding extends this documentation discipline to more Nations that ask for it: responsible disclosure done properly, every fact sourced, and the method shared so members can carry their own transparency work. The work is built to be repeatable, not one-off, and to strengthen independent, member-led efforts like the Transparency Circle rather than to substitute for them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="fund-more">
    <p class="fund-more__k">More from this program</p>
    <div class="fund-more__links">
      <a href="/disclosure/sagamok-portal">Responsible disclosure</a>
      <a href="https://rhtcircle.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Transparency Circle</a>
      <a href="/support">Support this program</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>
{% endblock %}
